content_vision: I watch my morning coffee while sipping the sunrise in my own garden on the porch of my house. I admire the moving shadows of apple trees gently swaying in the wind. I enjoy the cool breeze on my face.
structure_suggestion_description: Normal folk song about morning coffee
text:
Verse 1:
Lost in my thoughts, I wonder what tomorrow holds,
but for now, I'll just let the wind take control.
With every sip, my mind fills with dreams, and I'll let them guide me,
wherever they may lead.
As I gaze at the world, my heart fills with wonder,
and I'll keep chasing my dreams, with every step I'll lumber.
Lost in the moment, but I don't mind, I'll keep chasing after what I find,
and as the world turns, I'll hold on tight, to every moment, every feeling, every sight.

Pre-Chorus 1:
With every sip, I'm transported to a different world,
one where I'm fearless and my dreams unfurl.

Chorus 1:
Lost in my coffee, but I've found my peace,
in this moment, my soul's release.
Lost in my coffee, but I've found my peace,
in this moment, my soul's release.

Verse 2:
As the steam rises, my heart follows suit, letting go of worries,
till I'm just a carefree pursuit.
Lost in the moment, but I don't mind, because in this garden,
all my worries unwind.
In this peaceful moment, my worries are silenced,
and my soul sings free, with every sip of this coffee.
In this peaceful moment, my worries are silenced,
and my soul sings free, with every sip of this coffee.

Pre-Chorus 2:
But as I take another sip, my courage starts to rise,
I'll face the day with my head held high, with the world as my prize.

Chorus 2:
In this moment, I am free, lost in my coffee,
I'll be anything I want to be.
In this moment, I am free, lost in my coffee,
finding solace in the simple, as the world gets rocky.

Chorus 3:
Lost in my coffee, but I've found my peace,
in this moment, my soul's release.
With every sip, I feel the world fade away,
and I'll keep chasing my dreams, come what may.

Bridge:
With every sip, I'll let my heart open up, and in this peaceful moment,
I'll find my strength to never give up.
With every sip, I'll hold on tight, to the simple moments,
that make my life bright.

Outro:
As the sun sets and the day comes to an end,
I hold onto the memories, my soul I'll defend.
Lost in my coffee, but I've found my peace,
and in this moment, all my troubles release.
